<TITLE> Govt agrees to fund RAB complexes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 13 (bdnews24.com)--The government will build seven complexes for the elite force Rapid Action Battalion (RAB) costing Tk 436 crore. The Executive Committee of the National Economic Council approved a total of eight projects on Tuesday worth Tk 1,251 crore, which will be totally financed by the government. Over one third of the total money was agreed to be spent on the RAB complexes. The Committee was chaired by prime minister Sheikh Hasina. Three projects put forward by the water resources ministry, involving protection of the river banks, got the green light. The projects of Jamuna River bank protection in Jamalpur and Sirajganj and another for protection of the Meghna river bank will cost Tk 366 crore, Tk 36 crore and Tk 156 respectively. An agriculture ministry project costing Tk 51 crore involving irrigation development and a shipping ministry project involving the procurement of a dredger, pilot boats and dispatch boats costing Tk 83 crore was also approved. A fisheries and livestock ministry project involving poverty reduction costing Tk 51 crore and a Tk 40 crore textile and jute ministry project for the upgrading of the Begumganj Textile Institute of Noakhali into a Textile Engineering College were also both agreed by the ECNEC. The meeting was attended by finance minister AMA Muhith, planning minister AK Khandaker, water resources minister Ramesh Chandra Sen, agriculture minister Matia Chowdhury, commerce minister Faruk Khan, communication minister Syed Abul Hossain, shipping minister Shahajan Khan, LGRD minister Syed Ashraful Islam among others
